b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48015.htm)  [Next](sbe48017.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n#### Being and consciousness are not one.\n\nHence mere Being does not alone constitute reality. And as the distinction\nbetween consciousness and its objects--which rests just on this relation of\nobject and that for which the object is--is proved by perception, the\nassertion that only consciousness has real existence is also disposed of.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: The true meaning of Svayamprakasatva](sbe48017.htm)\n\n'